Our eyes have been glued to the TV for the last week – how about you 👀

Here are some of our highlights from the final week of @fifawomensworldcup group stages 👇

🇯🇵 Japan’s Hinta Miyazawa leads the tournament for most goals scored
🇸🇪 Sweden scoring three goals in the first six minutes of the match on their way to a 5-0 victory
🇵🇸 Heeba Saadieh takes the pitch as the first Palestinian FIFA World Cup referee
🇨🇴🇩🇪 Colombian and German fans unite celebrating both teams before their qualifying match
🇿🇲 Zambia scores the 1000th goal for the FIFA Women’s World Cup
🇯🇲 Reggae Girlz winning hearts and dancing into the round of 16, a first for the island nation
🇨🇴 Colombia qualifies with 6 goals in top position of Group H
🎟️ 1.7M tickets sold for group stage matches eclipsing the previous record of 1.35M

📸FIFA/Getty

“Football bringing people together is beautiful” 🫶

Moments to remember from week one of @fifawomensworldcup 👀 

🇨🇴 Linda Caicedo joining the ranks of legendary footballers to score in their World Cup debut 
🇵🇭 Philippines historic debut as the first team to represent the nation on a World Cup stage and celebrating their first win 
🇩🇪 6 goals by Germany, the highest in a single match thus far
🇮🇹 Italy’s 87th minute winner over Argentina 
🇯🇵 Japan becomes the first federation to secure a spot in round of 16 
 
#FIFAWWC

We’re coming together to move for the planet.

Starting June 1, for every 10 minutes of movement tracked in the adidas running app, we’ll donate €1 to @CommonGoalorg – up to €1.5m.

Whether it’s providing training on how to reduce plastic waste in sports facilities or renewing a community’s sports pitch using recycled materials, our collective movement means collective change.

This means we need YOUR help.

Choose from 34 sports – running to rugby, American football to basketball – it doesn’t matter how we move, just that we move.

#MoveForThePlanet

Someone pass us a pen, because we just rewrote the history books. ✍️

Thank you, 2023. 🙏

#ImpossibleIsNothing
@coachella /// Weekend 1

In 2022, Kenyan marathon runner @peresjepchirchirngeno officially made history after her victory at the Boston Marathon by becoming the first woman to capture all 3 winning titles - Boston, New York and the Olympics.

Never giving up on her aspirations and passion for running, her journey serves as a testament to perseverance and belief in oneself.

Head to our YouTube to watch Peres tell her inspiring life story in her own words.
 #ImpossibleIsNothing

When he needed to go higher than what was possible, Dick Fosbury created a new way of jumping.

And the “Fosbury Flop” was born, forever changing the high jump and cementing his legacy in track and field.

Today, we remember a true innovator who showed us all that Impossible Is Nothing.

Happy Monday to everyone but especially @mikaelashiffrin for becoming the most winningest World Cup alpine skier of all time. 

8️⃣7️⃣ and counting. 

#ImpossibleIsNothing

A reset for the history books, 34 years in the making. @mikaelashiffrin, you are something else.

🎉 87-time Alpine World Cup winner
🎹 Pianist
🥇 Two-time Olympic gold medalist
🎤 Singer

Our hero.

She soars to new heights at every opportunity, inspiring future generations to dream big and love their own journeys. We can’t wait to see what she accomplishes next. 🤍

#ImpossibleIsNothing

We’re coming together to move for the planet.

Starting June 1, for every 10 minutes of movement tracked in the adidas running app, we’ll donate €1 to @CommonGoalorg – up to €1.5m.

Whether it’s providing training on how to reduce plastic waste in sports facilities or renewing a community’s sports pitch using recycled materials, our collective movement means collective change.

This means we need YOUR help.

Choose from 34 sports – running to rugby, American football to basketball – it doesn’t matter how we move, just that we move.

#MoveForThePlanet

In 2022, Kenyan marathon runner @peresjepchirchirngeno officially made history after her victory at the Boston Marathon by becoming the first woman to capture all 3 winning titles - Boston, New York and the Olympics.

Never giving up on her aspirations and passion for running, her journey serves as a testament to perseverance and belief in oneself.

And the “Fosbury Flop” was born, forever changing the high jump and cementing his legacy in track and field.

Today, we remember a true innovator who showed us all that Impossible Is Nothing.

@packer’s long standing collaborative relationship with Reebok continues, this time honoring Allen Iverson’s illustrious legacy through his first signature shoe, the Question Mid.
 
AI brought a new sense of style to the game and the Packer for Reebok Question Mid replicates that flair through OG blocking with a twist. With a subtle design detail pulled from our Club C, each pair of Questions also incorporates mismatched upper panels that alternate between smooth, premium garment leather and full grain tumbled leather.
 
Burgundy suede accents combine with an icy blue outsole to contrast the intertwining crisp white textures. Two sets of laces — white and cream — along with co-branded insoles round out each pair.
 
The Packer for Reebok Question Mid releases exclusively at Packer on Friday, August 4th, at 11am EST online & in store.

Introducing the Reebok x @veefriends Aspiring Alpaca Classic Nylon, the shoe ready to take you wherever you aspire to go.
 
For this first-time partnership, VeeFriends and Reebok were honored to highlight a few remarkable VeeFriends community members. Community members @katzness, @christian.robles, and @sameasmemusic each exemplified the essence of Aspiring Alpaca in their own unique way.
 
 VeeFriends Presale begins August 17th 
 Available everywhere August 24th at 12am ET

@packer’s long standing collaborative relationship with Reebok continues, this time honoring Allen Iverson’s illustrious legacy through his first signature shoe, the Question Mid.
 
AI brought a new sense of style to the game and the Packer for Reebok Question Mid replicates that flair through OG blocking with a twist. With a subtle design detail pulled from our Club C, each pair of Questions also incorporates mismatched upper panels that alternate between smooth, premium garment leather and full grain tumbled leather.
 
Burgundy suede accents combine with an icy blue outsole to contrast the intertwining crisp white textures. Two sets of laces — white and cream — along with co-branded insoles round out each pair.
 
The Packer for Reebok Question Mid releases exclusively at Packer on Friday, August 4th, at 11am EST online & in store.
